Pre-Game Insights: Finidi George made three changes to the Super Eagles lineup for the Benin Republic clash, dropping Kelechi Iheanacho and including Raphael Onyedika and Samuel Chukwueze.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Super Eagles are looking for their first win of the series after drawing 1-1 against South Africa in their world cup qualifiers game.
Others: The starting lineup for the Super Eagles vs Benin Republic is: Stanley Nwabali, Calvin Bassey, Semi Ajayi, Benjamin Tanimu, Bright Osayi, Wilfred Ndidi (Captain), Raphael Onyedika, Alex Iwobi, Ademola Lookman, Terem Moffi, Samuel Chukwueze.
Other details: The game will start by 5pm Nigerian time.
